From: hmaarrfk <mark.harfouche@conda-forge.org>
Date: 2026-05-25
Subject: umd: do not add -g to Release builds

umd/CMakeLists.txt unconditionally appends -g to the Release flags:

    set(CMAKE_C_FLAGS_RELEASE   "${CMAKE_C_FLAGS_RELEASE} -g")
    set(CMAKE_CXX_FLAGS_RELEASE "${CMAKE_CXX_FLAGS_RELEASE} -g")

The top-level CMakeLists.txt defaults CMAKE_BUILD_TYPE to Release, so
every build is effectively RelWithDebInfo and the driver ships with full
DWARF. For libze_intel_npu.so that is ~17 MB of .debug_* sections on top
of ~1.4 MB of actual code: the installed library is 18.9 MB instead of
1.4 MB (conda-build does not strip it), and the LTO link has to merge all
of that debug info, which slows the build.

The debug info is never mapped at runtime (non-ALLOC sections), so it has
no functional value in a distributed runtime package; if debug symbols
are wanted they belong in a separate artifact, not the main library. Drop
the -g additions and let the Release optimisation flags stand on their
own.

Paths in this patch are prefixed with `linux-npu-driver-1.32.1/`
because conda-build extracts this source with `no_hoist: true` and
applies patches from the recipe's work_dir (one level above the
upstream root).
---
 linux-npu-driver-1.32.1/umd/CMakeLists.txt | 3 ---
 1 file changed, 3 deletions(-)
diff --git a/linux-npu-driver-1.32.1/umd/CMakeLists.txt b/linux-npu-driver-1.32.1/umd/CMakeLists.txt
index 7e92d47..170f3ac 100644
--- a/linux-npu-driver-1.32.1/umd/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/linux-npu-driver-1.32.1/umd/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -34,9 +34,6 @@ else()
     add_compile_options(-Wno-unused-but-set-variable -Wno-unused-variable)
 endif()

-set(CMAKE_C_FLAGS_RELEASE "${CMAKE_C_FLAGS_RELEASE} -g")
-set(CMAKE_CXX_FLAGS_RELEASE "${CMAKE_CXX_FLAGS_RELEASE} -g")
-
 set(CMAKE_CXX_FLAGS_DEBUG "${CMAKE_CXX_FLAGS_DEBUG} -DUMD_LOGLEVEL=${UMD_LOGLEVEL}")

 set(CMAKE_CXX_STANDARD 17)
--
2.54.0
